1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,171
Conquer luck excusitis in two ways.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:07,971
Number one, accept the law of cause and effect.

3
00:00:08,320 --> 00:00:12,370
Take a second look at what appears to be someone's good luck.

4
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:20,051
You'll find that not luck, but preparation, planning, and success-producing thinking preceded his good fortune.

5
00:00:20,401 --> 00:00:24,051
Take a second look at what appears to be someone's bad luck.

6
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:27,730
Look, and you'll discover certain specific reasons.

7
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,611
Mr. Success receives a setback.

8
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:32,611
He learns and profits.

9
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:37,171
But when Mr. Mediocre loses, he fails to learn.

10
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:41,651
Number two, don't be a wishful thinker.

11
00:00:41,921 --> 00:00:46,850
Don't waste your mental muscles dreaming of an effortless way to win success.

12
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:50,131
We don't become successful simply through luck.

13
00:00:50,401 --> 00:00:56,451
Success comes from doing those things and mastering those principles that produce success.

14
00:00:56,800 --> 00:01:01,411
Don't count on luck for promotions, victories, the good things in life.

15
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:05,730
Luck simply isn't designed to deliver these good things.

16
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:13,411
Instead, just concentrate on developing those qualities in yourself that will make you a winner.

